like him in
the media.

28:16.161 --> 28:20.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Moreover, without his dad
guiding him, Matt
would get lost here in hurry.

28:20.132 --> 28:25.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's why he's still lives at
home, a grown
man, with parents who are no
longer young,

28:25.304 --> 28:29.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and a mother who represents his
closest connection
to anyone.

28:29.942 --> 28:36.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You can see that so easily,
what's between
them.

28:36.248 --> 28:38.283 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But there's another side to this
connection.

28:38.317 --> 28:43.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's knowing that it may never
be duplicated,
and that no one else may have
Matt's back

28:44.022 --> 28:45.324 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like this.

28:45.357 --> 28:51.096 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK, Mother of Matt
Resnik: I do
worry about Matt.

28:51.129 --> 28:55.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I worry because he is so
trusting and so vulnerable.

28:55.701 --> 29:01.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I worry about, who is going to
be in his home
or help him and who is going to
understand

29:01.940 --> 29:03.342 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
him and all his idiosyncrasies?

29:03.375 --> 29:05.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And will I be there?

29:05.510 --> 29:07.446 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Let's sit over here.

29:07.479 --> 29:12.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: And how Denise has
responded
to that worry, one that is
shared by all parents

29:12.050 --> 29:17.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of all children facing such
challenges, it's
left its mark, and not just in
her house,

29:17.656 --> 29:21.893 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but in a much bigger way.

29:21.927 --> 29:26.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Although changing the world was
the farthest
thing from her mind back when
Matt was first

29:26.198 --> 29:29.301 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
diagnosed with autism in the
early 1990s.

29:29.334 --> 29:31.770 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then, the mission looked like
this.

29:31.803 --> 29:37.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: He was going to
be one of those
kids who recovered from his
autism.

29:37.476 --> 29:38.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I was sure of it.

29:38.510 --> 29:40.345 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was going to make sure that
that happened.

29:40.379 --> 29:42.247 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: And here's what
that meant.

29:42.280 --> 29:46.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: Immediately after
Matt's diagnosis,
I poured my heart and soul and
every waking

29:46.852 --> 29:53.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hour into making sure that we
were going to
provide Matt 40 hours of
one-on-one therapy

29:53.225 --> 29:59.631 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
every week, then artfully
integrate speech
therapy and art therapy and
riding therapy.

29:59.665 --> 30:04.002 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN DONVAN: Denise also
followed the path
taken by many other parents
before her, in

30:04.036 --> 30:09.207 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
other times and places, helping
to launch
an organization, the Southwest
Autism Research

30:09.241 --> 30:11.376 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and Resource Center, SARRC for
short.

30:11.410 --> 30:15.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: This is our
classroom play
area, and this is where a lot of
learning

30:15.380 --> 30:17.049 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
takes place.

30:17.082 --> 30:20.752 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: Which would bring
about, she
hoped, the rescue she was
praying for.

30:20.786 --> 30:23.088 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That essentially was the mission
back then.

30:23.121 --> 30:25.557 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DENISE RESNIK: We do our
research right here.

30:25.590 --> 30:30.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: SARRC even launched
its own scientific
research center and studied and
developed

30:30.529 --> 30:32.431 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
autism-specific curricula.

30:32.464 --> 30:36.101 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was an all-out campaign that
lasted years.

30:36.134 --> 30:39.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The only thing was, Matt did not
recover from
autism.

30:39.838 --> 30:44.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The available therapies can lead
to dramatically
different results in different
people.

30:44.176 --> 30:46.278 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And in Matt's case, he did make
strides.

30:46.311 --> 30:51.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He learned to bike and to hike
and to read
some words and multiply numbers
in his head,

30:51.683 --> 30:54.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which came in handy when he
helped his mom
bake.

30:54.152 --> 30:59.024 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But some things got worse, like
his eating
habits, chewing on things that
were not food.

30:59.057 --> 31:01.760 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: He would eat
things that were
not edible.

31:01.793 --> 31:06.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In a year, he chewed through 132
shirts.

31:06.998 --> 31:11.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: Nor did Matt ever
learn to recognize
danger in the usual sense.

31:11.770 --> 31:16.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even now, he wouldn't know what
to do if,
say, something in the oven
caught fire.

31:16.942 --> 31:19.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And his language still has
serious limits.

31:19.411 --> 31:25.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has never in his life asked a
question
or put together a spoken
sentence of his own

31:25.283 --> 31:31.089 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
making.

31:31.123 --> 31:38.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He never could talk the way he
could sing,
even back then, when Denise was
still counting

31:38.897 --> 31:44.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on this little kid outgrowing
the challenges
to his having a place of his own
in the world

31:44.202 --> 31:50.008 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
out there.

31:50.041 --> 31:55.147 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And over time, Denise came to
the realization
that it was the world out there
that would

31:55.180 --> 32:00.752 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have to change if Matt was to be
safe and
supported when his mom and dad
were gone.

32:00.786 --> 32:05.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Accepting that reality, in time,
Denise shifted
SARRC's mission in a new
direction.

32:05.624 --> 32:10.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: For the last two
decades, I
have poured my heart and soul
into trying

32:10.996 --> 32:16.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to build a community with a lot
of other people,
in trying to achieve a vision.

32:16.601 --> 32:20.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: And when you say
community, you
don't just mean a community of
the people

32:20.972 --> 32:22.507 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
directly affected by autism.

32:22.541 --> 32:24.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: Oh, I mean a
broader community.

32:24.342 --> 32:25.377 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN DONVAN: Everybody.

32:25.410 --> 32:27.279 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DENISE RESNIK: Right.

32:27.312 --> 32:31.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: And it's why
Phoenix, Arizona,
SARRC's hometown, may be the
most autism-aware,

32:31.683 --> 32:37.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
autism-friendly metropolis in
the world, one
in which everywhere Denise
pointed when we

32:37.255 --> 32:41.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rode the light rail through
downtown together,
there was a business employing
autistic people.

32:41.760 --> 32:43.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: And this is CVS
pharmacy.

32:43.261 --> 32:46.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: Or a school with
classes designed
with autism in mind.

32:46.665 --> 32:47.999 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: You can see ASU.

32:48.033 --> 32:50.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: Or research centers
investigating
treatments.

32:50.769 --> 32:52.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: St. Joseph
Hospital and Medical
Center.

32:52.838 --> 32:57.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: SARRC now has
literally dozens
and dozens of private and public
partners

32:57.609 --> 33:02.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
energized about supporting
autism in real
ways, and not just with money,
but with jobs,

33:02.747 --> 33:07.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
access and housing, some of it
captured in
the story we told last night
about that pilot

33:07.552 --> 33:12.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
program preparing autistic
adults to live
on their own and hold jobs, and
also this

33:12.991 --> 33:21.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
preschool, which mixes classes
of autistic
with non-autistic children,
because -- and

33:21.499 --> 33:25.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's with that mission in mind
again -- consider
what happens when all these kids
grow up.

33:25.503 --> 33:27.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DANIEL OPENDEN, President,
Southwest Autism
Research &amp; Resource Center: They
are inclusive

33:27.372 --> 33:30.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of kids that are different or
that have autism
or that have disabilities out on
the playground.

33:31.009 --> 33:31.977 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're future employers.

33:32.010 --> 33:33.111 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're future co-workers.

33:33.144 --> 33:36.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, we're not having to teach
these kids directly.

33:36.081 --> 33:39.251 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're just consumed around
people who are
different from them.

33:39.284 --> 33:43.755 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: And that is the big
picture that
Denise has long had in mind, a
world where

33:43.788 --> 33:47.726 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
support doesn't merely mean paid
staff providing
services.

33:47.759 --> 33:51.096 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It means, well, having neighbors
who care,
having friends.

33:51.129 --> 33:57.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: What people like
Matt and others
need, and what we need, are
communities, communities

33:57.936 --> 34:04.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that include friends, people to
support us,
health care, jobs, recreation,
places of worship,

34:04.075 --> 34:05.777 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
transportation.

34:05.810 --> 34:13.318 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And to think that a family can
go at this
alone to build a life for their
loved one

34:13.351 --> 34:15.086 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
isn't good enough.

34:15.120 --> 34:19.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: So, even if a
family had all
the money in the world, that --
having those

34:20.025 --> 34:24.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
resources would not be enough to
take care
of their kid through adulthood
and through

34:24.996 --> 34:26.765 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
life?

34:26.798 --> 34:30.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: It would be
enough to take
care of their kid, but what they
may be lacking

34:30.835 --> 34:33.638 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are friends, because you don't
pay your friends.

34:33.672 --> 34:39.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: The next major
step, well, it's
an empty lot right now, but it
won't always

34:39.344 --> 34:41.112 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
be.

34:41.146 --> 34:43.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when you come out here, do
you -- it is
an empty field now, but do --
can you see

34:43.481 --> 34:44.449 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it?

34:44.482 --> 34:45.450 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: I can see it.

34:45.483 --> 34:46.451 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN DONVAN: Yes?

34:46.484 --> 34:47.452 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: I can see it.

34:47.485 --> 34:48.453 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I can feel it.

34:48.486 --> 34:50.255 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it is going to happen.

34:50.288 --> 34:52.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's something I have been
dreaming about
almost since the first day the
school bus

34:52.490 --> 34:54.225 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
arrived for Matt.

34:54.259 --> 34:57.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: This is the future
site of an
apartment complex to be called
First Place,

34:58.029 --> 35:03.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
which will look like this, and
will be supported
by a collaboration among than 75
charitable,

35:03.969 --> 35:09.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
private and public groups,
creating a neighborhood
of people of varying levels of
ability and

35:09.274 --> 35:12.610 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
disability with more or less
support as needed.

35:12.644 --> 35:13.878 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It is where Matt will live too.

35:13.912 --> 35:16.448 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DENISE RESNIK: This is going to
be his home.

35:16.481 --> 35:21.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It may not be his home forever,
but aptly
named, it's going to be his home
when he leaves

35:21.419 --> 35:22.387 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our family home.

35:22.420 --> 35:23.455 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: His first place
away from home.

35:23.488 --> 35:24.689 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DENISE RESNIK: It is.

35:24.723 --> 35:28.660 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: Ground-breaking is
set for later
this year.

35:28.693 --> 35:33.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For now, though, Matt still has
the two best
support people anyone could ask
for, his mom

35:33.064 --> 35:37.936 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and dad, who are helping keep
the biscotti
business on track, one that
employs several

35:37.969 --> 35:42.507 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
people on the autism spectrum.

35:42.540 --> 35:46.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But when it's just the three of
them together,
that's when the question of
Matt's future

35:46.611 --> 35:52.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
comes back into focus, with the
hope that
10, 20, 30, 40 years from now,
he will have

35:52.384 --> 35:59.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a whole community by his side
and at his back,
taking in the song, and caring
what he has

35:59.224 --> 36:00.959 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to say.

36:00.992 --> 36:07.132 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MATT RESNIK (singing): And I'm
free, free-falling.

36:07.165 --> 36:14.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN DONVAN: For the "PBS
NewsHour," I'm John
Donvan in Phoenix.

36:14.472 --> 36:24.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We have reported
at length
for more than a year on the
migrant crisis

36:24.516 --> 36:29.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We have reported
at length
for more than a year on the
migrant crisis

36:29.521 --> 36:31.890 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Europe, the Middle East and
North Africa.

36:31.923 --> 36:36.928 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, tonight, we look at the
plight of those
searching for new homes and
lives far away

36:36.961 --> 36:38.630 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from those shores.

36:38.663 --> 36:40.398 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Hari Sreenivasan has that.

36:40.432 --> 36:43.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The government
of Australia
has, for years now, made it very
clear that

36:43.968 --> 36:49.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they will no longer accept
refugees and migrants
coming to the continent by boat.

36:49.174 --> 36:54.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And those that do are sent to a
tiny island
nation called Nauru off
Australia's northeast

36:54.212 --> 36:56.047 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
coast.

36:56.081 --> 37:00.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But recent reports by human
rights advocates,
and today from The Guardian
newspaper, show

37:00.285 --> 37:06.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nightmarish conditions for more
than 1,000
people who were sent for
processing by Australia's

37:06.291 --> 37:09.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
government to this island
nation.

37:09.294 --> 37:14.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Allegations in the report
include physical
and sexual abuse, often aimed at
children,

37:14.165 --> 37:17.368 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and substandard and inhumane
living conditions.

37:17.402 --> 37:22.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For more on this, I'm joined
from Paris by
Anna Neistat of Amnesty
International.

37:22.607 --> 37:24.075 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Thanks for being with us.

37:24.109 --> 37:26.377 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is a hard place to get to.

37:26.411 --> 37:30.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You gained access where many
journalists have
not been able to.

37:30.582 --> 37:32.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tell us what you saw when you
got to this
island.

37:32.550 --> 37:37.322 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ANNA NEISTAT, Amnesty
International: What
I saw there can only be
described as deliberate

37:37.355 --> 37:40.525 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
systematic abuse.

37:40.558 --> 37:43.027 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We're not talking about
individual incidents.

37:43.061 --> 37:46.498 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the files released today
make it crystal-clear.

37:46.531 --> 37:53.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are talking about patterns,
patterns of
really serious physical
conditions, heart

37:53.371 --> 37:58.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
diseases, complications from
diabetes, kidney
diseases that are not being
treated properly,

37:58.843 --> 38:03.815 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and for which people are not
being transferred
elsewhere to get proper care.

38:03.848 --> 38:11.422 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And probably the most
nightmarish of it all
is the state of psychological
trauma and the

38:11.456 --> 38:18.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rate of self-harm and attempted
suicides amongst
adults, but even worse among
children.

38:18.730 --> 38:24.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I personally interviewed several
children,
including a boy as young as 9,
who already

38:24.402 --> 38:28.606 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
attempted suicide and was still
talking about
