39:44.515 --> 39:48.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And many people of the people --
so many of
the people employed by the
companies who work

39:48.253 --> 39:49.954 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on Nauru are local.

39:49.988 --> 39:56.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: This is part
of Australia's
policy to not allow any of these
migrants

39:56.594 --> 39:59.197 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
or refugees to settle on
Australian soil.

39:59.230 --> 40:02.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're keeping them off the
continent for
a reason.

40:02.600 --> 40:08.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say that this is to create
a disincentive,
so more refugees don't get on
boats and you

40:08.940 --> 40:11.876 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
don't see what's been happening
between the
Middle East and Europe.

40:11.909 --> 40:16.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANNA NEISTAT: Well, yes, and I
think that's
one of the most cynical refugee
policies I

40:16.814 --> 40:18.182 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
have ever seen.

40:18.216 --> 40:20.885 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Australia is indeed quite
open about that.

40:20.919 --> 40:25.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They are essentially making an
example of
these people, so that the ones
-- the ones

40:25.323 --> 40:31.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that are held in Nauru, so that
others do
not attempt the same route, do
not arrive

40:31.095 --> 40:34.198 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to arrive to Australia by boat.

40:34.232 --> 40:42.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think this is not only
unlawful, but
it also again goes against any
principles

40:42.173 --> 40:43.808 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of humanity.

40:43.841 --> 40:48.813 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What they have spent enormous
effort on is
keeping this whole situation
secret.

40:48.846 --> 40:50.581 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

40:50.615 --> 40:54.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's why many of your viewers,
I'm sure,
have never heard about this
situation, is

40:54.085 --> 40:55.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
